</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"body-el-text standard-body-el-text\">Coffee’s original name, <em>qahwah</em>, came from the Yemen term for wine. In Turkey it was called <em>kahveh</em>, until the Dutch referred to it as <em>koffie</em>, where we get the English <em>coffee</em>.</p>", "Fun Facts About Coffee", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "29-revision-v1", "", "", "2016-12-21 23:16:43", "2016-12-22 04:16:43", "", "29", "http://localhost/index.php/2016/12/21/29-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("31", "1", "2016-12-21 23:19:29", "2016-12-22 04:19:29", "<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-307\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i1.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/10a682.jpg?resize=267%2C189&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 267px) 100vw, 267px\" alt=\"10\" width=\"267\" height=\"189\" />\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Coffee</strong><strong> Improves Energy Levels and Can Make You Smarter</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nCaffeine blocks an inhibitory neurotransmitter in the brain, which leads to a stimulant effect. This improves energy levels, mood and various aspects of brain function.\r\n\r\n2. <strong>Coffee</strong><strong> Can Help You Burn Fat</strong>\r\n\r\nSeveral studies show that caffeine can increase fat burning in the body and boost the metabolic rate.\r\n\r\n3. <strong>Caffeine</strong><strong> Can Drastically Improve Physical Performance</strong>\r\n\r\nCaffeine can increase adrenaline levels and release fatty acids from the fat tissues. It also leads to significant improvements in physical performance.\r\n\r\n4. <strong>There</strong><strong> Are Essential Nutrients in Coffee</strong>\r\n\r\nCoffee contains several important nutrients; including Riboflavin, Pantothenic Acid, Manganese, Potassium, Magnesium and Niacin.\r\n\r\n5. <strong>Coffee</strong><strong> Lowers Risk of Type II Diabetes</strong>\r\n\r\nSeveral observational studies show that coffee drinkers have a much lower risk of getting Type II Diabetes, a serious disease that currently afflicts about 300 million people worldwide.\r\n\r\n<strong>   6. </strong><strong>Coffee</strong><strong> Helps Reduce Risk of Alzheimer’s Disease and Dementia</strong>\r\n\r\nCoffee drinkers have much lower risk of getting Alzheimer’s disease, which is a leading cause of Dementia worldwide.\r\n\r\n<strong>   7. Caffeine Helps Lower Risk of Parkinson’s Disease</strong>\r\n\r\nCoffee drinkers have up to a 60% lower risk of getting Parkinson’s disease; the second most common neurodegenerative disorder.\r\n\r\n<strong>   8. Coffee Has Protective Affects on The Liver</strong>\r\n\r\nCoffee drinkers have much lower risk of developing cirrhosis; which can be caused by several diseases that affect the liver.\r\n\r\n<strong>   9. Coffee Helps Fight Depression and Make You Happier</strong>\r\n\r\nCoffee appears to lower the risk of developing depression and may dramatically reduce the risk of suicide.\r\n\r\n10. <strong>Coffee</strong><strong> Drinkers Have a Lower Risk of Some Types of Cancer</strong>\r\n\r\nLiver and colorectal cancer are the 3rd and 4th leading causes of cancer deaths worldwide. Coffee drinkers have a lower risk of both.\r\n\r\n11. <strong>Coffee</strong><strong> Does Not Cause Heart Disease and Helps Lower Risk of Stroke</strong>\r\n\r\nCoffee may cause mild increases in blood pressure, which usually diminish over time. Coffee drinkers do not have an increased risk of Heart disease, but a lower risk of Stroke.\r\n\r\n<strong>   12. Coffee May Help You Live Longer</strong>\r\n\r\nSeveral studies show that coffee drinkers live longer and have a lower risk of premature death.\r\n\r\n13. <strong>Coffee</strong><strong> is The Biggest Source of Antioxidants in the Western Diet</strong>\r\n\r\nCoffee is one of the healthiest beverages on the planet; period.", "13 Health Benefits of Coffee", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "13-health-benefits-of-coffee", "", "", "2016-12-21 23:19:29", "2016-12-22 04:19:29", "", "0", "http://localhost/?p=31", "0", "post", "", "0");
