INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("33", "1", "2016-12-21 23:22:57", "2016-12-22 04:22:57", "<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Keep Slugs Away</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-194\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-17999-1411655088-15711e.jpg?resize=625%2C469&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-17999-1411655088-15\" width=\"625\" height=\"469\" /></li>\r\n 	<li>Unlike worms, slugs, snails, and other bugs don’t like the acidity of coffee and won’t cross the ground if it’s sprinkled with java.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n2. <strong>Keep</strong><strong> Your Cat In Or Other Cats Out Of Your Yard</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-204\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i1.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-3014-1411656269-217a12.jpg?resize=625%2C352&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-3014-1411656269-21\" width=\"625\" height=\"352\" />\r\n\r\nTired of waiting hours for your cat to return; or your neighbors cats traipsing through your flowers? Just sprinkle some coffee grounds and orange peel where you don’t want them to walk.\r\n\r\n3. <strong>Make</strong><strong> A Roach Trap</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-207\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-8580-1411657401-146813.jpg?resize=625%2C417&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-8580-1411657401-14\" width=\"625\" height=\"417\" />\r\n\r\nFill a can or jar with an inch or two of moistened coffee grounds, then line the container’s neck with extra-sticky double-sided tape. The scent will draw cockroaches into the trap.\r\n\r\n4. <strong>Unclog</strong><strong> Your Drain</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-209\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-19617-1411658722-476813.jpg?resize=625%2C417&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-19617-1411658722-47\" width=\"625\" height=\"417\" />\r\n\r\nPour used coffee grounds down the sink or bathtub drain, followed by 3 drops of dish soap and a pot of boiling water. This will clean and clear the drain of clogs and built up grease.\r\n\r\n5. <strong>No</strong><strong> Bake Energy Bites</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-212\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-6807-1411663026-86813.jpg?resize=625%2C417&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-6807-1411663026-8\" width=\"625\" height=\"417\" />\r\n\r\nStir your oatmeal, flaxseed, and coffee granules together in a medium bowl until thoroughly mixed, then add your almond butter(or peanut butter), honey, and vanilla. Once well combined fold in your chocolate chips and cranberries. Stir well!  Let chill in the refrigerator for 20 minutes.  Once chilled, roll into balls of whatever size you would like, I usually make 10-12 balls. Store in an airtight container and keep in the fridge for up to 1 week…if they last that long!\r\n\r\n6. <strong>Make</strong><strong> A Flea Bath</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-215\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-28939-1411661041-23b052.jpg?resize=625%2C447&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-28939-1411661041-23\" width=\"625\" height=\"447\" />\r\n\r\nAdd some coffee grounds to your dog’s shampoo to create a natural flea repellant.\r\n\r\n7. <strong>Strip</strong><strong> Build-up From Your Hair</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-217\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i0.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-26160-1411662206-21b27a.jpg?resize=625%2C415&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-26160-1411662206-21\" width=\"625\" height=\"415\" />\r\n\r\nThe abrasive texture of coffee grounds will help strip oils and buildup from your hair. Pile them on in the shower or, for a much less messy strategy, just add some grounds to your shampoo or conditioner. Caution: best for brunettes as coffee can also darken hair.\r\n\r\n8. <strong>Make</strong><strong> A Luxurious Salt Scrub</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i0.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-1108-1411663736-276813.jpg?resize=625%2C417&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-1108-1411663736-27\" width=\"625\" height=\"417\" />\r\n\r\nIn a large bowl, add coarse sea salt and coffee grounds and stir; place oil and essential oils into bowl and stir.  Store in air tight jar and use for those days when you need to need a good scrubbing.\r\n\r\n9. <strong>Make</strong><strong> A Mocha Frappuccino Mask</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-224\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i0.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-25481-1411661970-34e4a8.jpg?resize=625%2C846&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-25481-1411661970-34\" width=\"625\" height=\"846\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>2 Tbsp freshly ground coffee</b></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>2 Tbsp. cocoa powder</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>3 Tbsp. milk (whole), heavy cream, or yogurt</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>1 Tbsp. honey</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMix all the ingredients together well. Apply to a sleepy morning face. Allow the mask to dry for 15-20 minutes. Wash off in the shower, scrubbing VERY lightly over the skin while rinsing.\r\n\r\n10. <strong>Salt</strong><strong> Your Sidewalk or Driveway</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i0.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-11691-1411664220-1711e.jpg?resize=625%2C469&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-11691-1411664220-1\" width=\"625\" height=\"469\" />\r\n\r\nCoffee grounds make great gravel to help keep roads and sidewalks from being slippery, and the acid helps melt the ice quicker.", "10 Ways You Can Reuse Your Old Coffee Grounds", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "10-ways-you-can-reuse-your-old-coffee-grounds", "", "", "2016-12-21 23:22:57", "2016-12-22 04:22:57", "", "0", "http://localhost/?p=33", "0", "post", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("34", "1", "2016-12-21 23:22:57", "2016-12-22 04:22:57", "<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Keep Slugs Away</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-194\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-17999-1411655088-15711e.jpg?resize=625%2C469&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-17999-1411655088-15\" width=\"625\" height=\"469\" /></li>\r\n 	<li>Unlike worms, slugs, snails, and other bugs don’t like the acidity of coffee and won’t cross the ground if it’s sprinkled with java.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n2. <strong>Keep</strong><strong> Your Cat In Or Other Cats Out Of Your Yard</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-204\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i1.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-3014-1411656269-217a12.jpg?resize=625%2C352&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-3014-1411656269-21\" width=\"625\" height=\"352\" />\r\n\r\nTired of waiting hours for your cat to return; or your neighbors cats traipsing through your flowers? Just sprinkle some coffee grounds and orange peel where you don’t want them to walk.\r\n\r\n3. <strong>Make</strong><strong> A Roach Trap</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-207\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-8580-1411657401-146813.jpg?resize=625%2C417&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-8580-1411657401-14\" width=\"625\" height=\"417\" />\r\n\r\nFill a can or jar with an inch or two of moistened coffee grounds, then line the container’s neck with extra-sticky double-sided tape. The scent will draw cockroaches into the trap.\r\n\r\n4. <strong>Unclog</strong><strong> Your Drain</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-209\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-19617-1411658722-476813.jpg?resize=625%2C417&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-19617-1411658722-47\" width=\"625\" height=\"417\" />\r\n\r\nPour used coffee grounds down the sink or bathtub drain, followed by 3 drops of dish soap and a pot of boiling water. This will clean and clear the drain of clogs and built up grease.\r\n\r\n5. <strong>No</strong><strong> Bake Energy Bites</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-212\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-6807-1411663026-86813.jpg?resize=625%2C417&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-6807-1411663026-8\" width=\"625\" height=\"417\" />\r\n\r\nStir your oatmeal, flaxseed, and coffee granules together in a medium bowl until thoroughly mixed, then add your almond butter(or peanut butter), honey, and vanilla. Once well combined fold in your chocolate chips and cranberries. Stir well!  Let chill in the refrigerator for 20 minutes.  Once chilled, roll into balls of whatever size you would like, I usually make 10-12 balls. Store in an airtight container and keep in the fridge for up to 1 week…if they last that long!\r\n\r\n6. <strong>Make</strong><strong> A Flea Bath</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-215\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-28939-1411661041-23b052.jpg?resize=625%2C447&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-28939-1411661041-23\" width=\"625\" height=\"447\" />\r\n\r\nAdd some coffee grounds to your dog’s shampoo to create a natural flea repellant.\r\n\r\n7. <strong>Strip</strong><strong> Build-up From Your Hair</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-217\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i0.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-26160-1411662206-21b27a.jpg?resize=625%2C415&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-26160-1411662206-21\" width=\"625\" height=\"415\" />\r\n\r\nThe abrasive texture of coffee grounds will help strip oils and buildup from your hair. Pile them on in the shower or, for a much less messy strategy, just add some grounds to your shampoo or conditioner. Caution: best for brunettes as coffee can also darken hair.\r\n\r\n8. <strong>Make</strong><strong> A Luxurious Salt Scrub</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i0.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-1108-1411663736-276813.jpg?resize=625%2C417&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-1108-1411663736-27\" width=\"625\" height=\"417\" />\r\n\r\nIn a large bowl, add coarse sea salt and coffee grounds and stir; place oil and essential oils into bowl and stir.  Store in air tight jar and use for those days when you need to need a good scrubbing.\r\n\r\n9. <strong>Make</strong><strong> A Mocha Frappuccino Mask</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-224\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i0.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-buzz-25481-1411661970-34e4a8.jpg?resize=625%2C846&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-buzz-25481-1411661970-34\" width=\"625\" height=\"846\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>2 Tbsp freshly ground coffee</b></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>2 Tbsp. cocoa powder</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>3 Tbsp. milk (whole), heavy cream, or yogurt</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>1 Tbsp. honey</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMix all the ingredients together well. Apply to a sleepy morning face. Allow the mask to dry for 15-20 minutes. Wash off in the shower, scrubbing VERY lightly over the skin while rinsing.\r\n\r\n10. <strong>Salt</strong><strong> Your Sidewalk or Driveway</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i0.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/enhanced-11691-1411664220-1711e.jpg?resize=625%2C469&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" alt=\"enhanced-11691-1411664220-1\" width=\"625\" height=\"469\" />\r\n\r\nCoffee grounds make great gravel to help keep roads and sidewalks from being slippery, and the acid helps melt the ice quicker.", "10 Ways You Can Reuse Your Old Coffee Grounds", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "33-revision-v1", "", "", "2016-12-21 23:22:57", "2016-12-22 04:22:57", "", "33", "http://localhost/index.php/2016/12/21/33-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("35", "1", "2016-12-21 23:24:35", "2016-12-22 04:24:35", "<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-141\" src=\"https://thecoffeebean813.github.io/i2.wp.com/coffeebean506.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/10ca18.png?resize=274%2C184&amp;ssl=1\" sizes=\"(max-width: 274px) 100vw, 274px\" alt=\"10\" width=\"274\" height=\"184\" />   In America, we consume over 400 million cups of coffee every day. Ever wonder why so many of us make such a lustful beeline for our caffeine?  Could it be the oodles of antioxidants it contains? Or that science has revealed its health benefits, including lowered risk of diabetes, Parkinson’s disease, gallstones, and colon cancer? I don’t think that even these unquestionable virtues are what make coffee the highlight of your day. Then what does? The mood and energy-enhancing effects of caffeine. Caffeine stimulates the central nervous system and acts as an antidepressant by elevating serotonin and dopamine–it’s even been shown in the Archives of Internal Medicine to lower suicide rates. Some experience the mood boost more than others. Unknowingly, many people self-medicate depression with caffeine. How to know if you’re doing this versus just getting a beneficial pick-me-up? Some tip-offs: You consume more than four caffeinated beverages daily, including teas and diet sodas. Or you keep increasing your caffeine intake to feel less depressed, but it’s losing its effectiveness. I’m all for making the most of coffee’s therapeutic perks to allay low-level depression, but sometimes you may need other approaches when this emotion still persists. To find out if you’re self-medicating depression, you can stop your caffeine intake. After a month (most withdrawal symptoms, which include headache and fatigue, will be over by then) notice if you’re notably more depressed without caffeine, not always an easy experiment. Should you discover that you are self-medicating, also consider the numerous therapies discussed in this chapter to augment coffee, or to replace it. However, mild depressions can respond well to simply drinking up to three cups daily. (Try spacing them out; caffeine remains in the system four to six hours). More than this increases side effects and raises the chances of tolerance and addiction: You consume greater quantities but don’t get the lift. Always consider caffeine’s pluses and minuses. Reduce your intake if you have insomnia, heartburn, palpitations, headaches, or nervousness. Moreover, if you’re being treated for heart disease, hypertension, gastrointestinal problems, or other chronic illnesses, consult your physician before you ingest caffeine; although recent studies show coffee helps reduce risk of some chronic illnesses.", "Depression & Coffee", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "depression-coffee", "", "", "2016-12-21 23:24:35", "2016-12-22 04:24:35", "", "0", "http://localhost/?p=35", "0", "post", "", "0");
